<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Explore fund types</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    Click <strong>Settings</strong> in the sidebar, then click <strong>Funds</strong>.
  </li>
  <li>
    You'll see 19 pre-configured fund types, including:
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Council Tax, Business Rates, Housing Rents</li>
      <li>Parking Fines, Fixed Penalty Notices</li>
      <li>Building Control, Development Control</li>
      <li>Library Charges, Market Stall Rental</li>
      <li>HMO Premises Licence, Landlord Accreditation</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    Click <strong>View</strong> on any fund to see its metadata — including the GOV.UK Pay API key configured for payment processing.
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Review system settings</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    Go back to <strong>Settings</strong> to see all 15 configuration areas:
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li><strong>MOP codes</strong> — payment methods (Cash, Card, Transfer, etc.)</li>
      <li><strong>Payment integrations</strong> — GOV.UK Pay connection settings</li>
      <li><strong>Roles</strong> — permission definitions for user access</li>
      <li><strong>Import types</strong> — bank file import configurations</li>
      <li><strong>VAT codes</strong> — tax rate mappings</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    Click <strong>Payment integrations</strong> to see the GOV.UK Pay integration endpoint configured with your CloudFront URL.
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <strong>Real-world context:</strong> Each council customises these settings for their specific income streams. Some councils manage 50+ fund types across multiple departments.
</div>
